<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1437,151,249]" box="[199,1244,151,177]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Color in life a solid, orange abactinal surface. Oral surface lighter orange to yellow (
<figureCitation box="[1145,1230,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="29.[151,250,1873,1897]" captionTargetBox="[183,1405,184,1848]" captionTargetId="figure-15@29.[182,1405,181,1849]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURE 9. Atheraster symphonium n. sp. Holotype. USNM 1467555. A. Abactinal surface. Scale bar=10.0 mm. B. Abactinal-lateral, showing spines on marginal plates. Scale bar=3.0 mm. C. Actinal surface. Scale bar=10.0 mm. D. Abactinal surface showing transition of plate size between disk and arm. Scale bar=3.0 mm. E. Furrow spines showing pedicellariae and adambulacral/actinal accessories. Scale bar=3.0 mm. F. Close-up of actinal surface showing intermediate regions and furrow spines. Scale bar=3.0 mm. G. In situ image of holotype, Sibelius Seamount, Musicians Seamounts, 2437 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6821052" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6821052/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
